I just made this again for the first time in years, even though I have a note that it's a great stand-by on the printed copy I have. I up the portion size and serve it as an entree with either little mashed potato or risotto patties that I mix up with a little egg and finely grated cheese. Chill them, then coat with panko and saute in olive oil until golden brown. They can then be put into the oven along with the shrimp to finish heating through while you make the sauce. They're both easy to make, and you can do all your prep in advance, then just whip it together a la minute. It impresses guests, and I love it!

