Want an easy, yet memorable dish to whip up? This is it. I agree with other reviewers about 2 helpful hints: 1) Saute the shrimp for 1-2 minutes, then pull out of pan into a bowl. Add them back after you finish the sauce and simmer for a couple more mintues to reheat. 2) Cut down the butter to 3-4 tbls - it's plenty. (And FYI: if you only have a lime, instead of a lemon, it works well.) Have a crusty bread available for cleaning up the sauce from your plate.

