Stop the presses - this one really ROCKS! It was sooo fast and one of the tastiest things I've ever eaten! I used a whole lb of large shrimp (16 count) and my S.O. and I ate it ALL! I served it over a small serving of very el dente fresh linguine with an oaky/buttery chardonnay and it was an unimaginable delight. I added a sprinkling of cayenne for some a touch of heat. I brined the shrimp for 15 mins before cooking (2 tbsp each salt and sugar in ice water - soak 15 mins then rinse and cook). I didnt precook the shrimp, I prepped the sauce then added the shrimp and cooked it over high heat for a scant few minutes (didnt add the basil till the very end. The shrimp were crisp, sweet and succulent. I very highly recommend this recipe.

